items.name: Valerian & Laureline Comic Style
items.description:
Valerian & Laureline

What is it?


It is trained from earlier images of Valerian & Laureline, which is a French science fiction comics series, created by writer Pierre Christin and artist Jean-Claude Mézières. It ran from 1967 to 2010. I recently discovered it and fell in love with the story and art style. So, I decided to try and recreate it. At the time it was first published, sci fi was not as mainstream of a concept as it is now. You will often find that many popular sci fi literature/movies have influence from the comic and setting. Somewhat of a grandfather to sci fi. This is my first attempt at recreating this style.

Recommended Value

I personally keep the weight between 0.4 to 0.6 with 0.6 being my personal favorite weight overall.

All my images within this card also used the DreamShaper model but works well with any model. It easy to recreate the aesthetic and style of the comic, however by playing with the prompt and different models. You can get some amazing cartoon/anime like results.

Bonus!

Deforum animation using this LoRA!

items.name: Kanna - Blaster Master
items.description:
A lora trained on 235 hand-picked images of Kanna from Blaster Master. It was AI tagged with e621 tags, however it seems to work much better using anime-based .ckpts like Anything 4.5 ...Still though, most models work pretty well with it. If using anime model as the base, try to avoid "looking" tags (looking at viewer, looking away, etc.), or else Kanna might appear to have more anime-styled eyes, and sometimes a nose (see example image #3). Using a full 1.0 weight value seems to do fine.

Some tags like "skintight" and "fishnets" might help achieve her usual outfit. It also handles nudity fine, but I did not include any example images.

I've included a .txt file including all the tags, it's in the "Training Data" download.

4/26 UPDATE:

I've trained a new lora on the same dataset, but on a different model than the first version: Fluffyrock.

Fluffyrock is a new "furry" image generation model that has caught my eye by it's surprising quality. It's a lot harder to work with than most anime models in my opinion, but I took the opportunity to train this lora as a test on the new model.

It was trained at 896x896 resolution, again though, using the exact same dataset as the original. It was trained on the fluffyrock 576-832 multires model epoch 20, however, it works well with any of the models, even the new 1088 resolution models.

Fluffyrock downloads: Here (All models) & Here (576-832 e20 recommened)

Notes:
-With the fluffyrock-trained lora, it's much higher resolution, meaning Kanna's eyes are a lot better at understanding expression

-Fluffyrock can handle artist tags quite well, so give them a shot!

-This lora does NOT work with anime-based models at all! Only use this with fluffyrock, use with other models will simply give abysmal results.

items.name: Shikimori (Kawaii dake ja Nai Shikimori-san)
items.description:
This is a character LoRA for Shikimori from Kawaii dake ja Nai Shikimori-san.

Version 2

This LoRA was trained on 21 handpicked images from gelbooru, zerochan, and pixiv with Anything v4.5. In this version, I reduced the number of fanart and added more screenshots from the anime into the dataset. This LoRA might be a little overcooked, but I think that its way better than the previous version.

To use this LoRA, include the trigger word shikimoriMicchon at a weight of around 0.75-0.85. No other descriptive words should be necessary! Consider using at a weight of 0.6-0.7 when mixing with other LoRAs.

  • To generate her school uniform, include the tags school uniform, black sweater, white shirt, red neck ribbon, and grey skirt with hair ribbon added to the negative prompts.

  • To generate her swimsuit, include the tags black crop top, cleavage, and denim shorts.

Version 1

This LoRA was trained on 19 handpicked images from gelbooru, zerochan, and pixiv with Anything v4.5.

To use this LoRA, include the trigger word shikimoriMicchon at a weight of around 0.75-1. Adding descriptive words like blue eyes and long hair should also help bring out the character's features.

  • To generate her school uniform, include the tags school uniform, white shirt, black sweater, neck ribbon, and grey skirt.

  • To generate her swimsuit, include the tags black crop top, collarbone, navel, and short shorts.


I'm looking forward to see what you all come up with. Be sure to leave feedback as comments and reviews!

items.name: FaeTastic
items.description:
FaeTastic

https://ko-fi.com/post/The-Double-Headed-Issue-E1E0JO2UV

PLEASE FOR THE LOVE OF GOD READ THIS TUTORIAL ABOVE IF YOU GET DOUBLE-HEADED THINGS

IF YOU ARE PUZZLED WHY YOU CAN'T 1:1 AN IMAGE PLEASE SEE THIS COMMENT: https://civitai.com/models/14065/faetastic?commentId=69125&modal=commentThread

A Versatile Mixed Model with Noise Offset

If you have time please make sure to read everything below!

Please make sure to download and use the included VAE!!! IF YOUR IMAGES ARE WASHED OUT, YOU NEED VAE! :)

This is my first model mix that was born from a failure of mine. I tried training a model on some generated images that I loved, but I did not love how it came out. Instead of tossing it I instead started to mix it into other models to produce 'FaeTastic'. :)

This model was mixed up 22 times to finally get an iteration that I loved. I hate when models don't 'listen' to you and also when they double up and produce some wacky stuff. While I'm not going to claim that this model is perfect, I think it just does a fantastic job at what I was trying to aim for.

The model is also extremely versatile, it can do beautiful landscapes, excels at semi-realistic characters, can do anime styles if you prompt it to (you need to weight anime tags though), can do NSFW, works beautifully with embeddings and LORAs and also has the fantastic noise offset built in to produce rich dark beautiful images, if you ask it to!

Model Genetics

The base came from a 1.5-trained model I made and then mixed in the following models as well as the base mix 22 times. These are the following models that were used:

Noise Offset for True Darkness

ReV Animated

The Ally's Mix III: Revolutions

2DN

Deliberate

Fae's Sad Model that Sucked by Itself

Sadly, I am not smart enough or knowledgeable enough to understand how much of each model stays into something when mixed up 22 times. Some models were mixed more than others and one model was only mixed in one time, etc. Regardless, I wanted to credit all of the models that were used. If my model doesn't tickle your fancy, then I highly recommend the above models as they are all wonderful and awesome too!

Why Aren't My Images Crisp Like Yours?

PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING GUIDE: https://ko-fi.com/post/The-Double-Headed-Issue-E1E0JO2UV

I am just going to put this here from the beginning, as I've been asked this question before regarding the textual inversions that I have made. Plus it might come in helpful for those that are just getting into AI Art, sometimes it's hard for people to remember when they themselves were noobs! :)

So, the answer to this question is that I generate my initial images with Hires. fix on, then take an image that I like, send it to img2img, and then upscale it further there with the SD upscale script.

This is an example of what my general settings are when generating initial txt2imgs. I also sometimes use Euler A, DPM++2MKarras, DDIM. I usually only do between 20-40 Sampling steps, usually keep CFG Scale between 10-12, and the Denoising Strength I usually keep between 0.3-0.45. For the upscale, I prefer using 4x Foolhardy Remacri or 4x UltraSharp.

Just play around and find what you personally enjoy yourself! :)

If you are still confused and not getting the results that you like, feel free to leave a comment on my model page or you can send me a message on discord, I am in the CivitAI discord! I'll do my best to help you! :)

My Images Aren't Coming out like Yours!

This could be a lot of reasons! I use xformers, I might have different A111 settings than yours, did you check the seed, did you check your VAE, do you accidentally have Clip skip 2 on, I only use Clip skip 1. I have ETA Noise seed delta set at 31337. It could be a lot of things! Regardless if you use the prompt and have all of the embeddings or LORAs included, then the results should be similar! If you still can't figure it out, feel free to comment on this page or message me in discord and we can try to troubleshoot together! :)

PLEASE SEE THIS COMMENT I REPLIED TO SOMEONE WITH FOR FURTHER EXPLANATION: https://civitai.com/models/14065/faetastic?commentId=69125&modal=commentThread

Textual Inversions/Embeddings and LORAs

Update 3/21/23 - I have removed all textual inversions and LORAs in my display pictures due to receiving too many questions and issues regarding them. I still highly recommend the below list for those that want to utilize them!

I am a huge fan of using embeddings and LORAs, they up your AI game and you should be using them! Below I am going to list all of the Textual Inversions/Embeddings, LORAs that I used for the display images. If I missed one, I deeply apologize and just post a comment and I'll update this page!

Nebula Magic

Sylva Magic

Rust Magic

EasyNegative (THIS GOES INTO YOUR NEGATIVE PROMPT)

Deep Negative V1.x (THIS GOES INTO YOUR NEGATIVE PROMPT)

Dollie Nobody

Bridal Style

Bad Prompt (THIS GOES INTO YOUR NEGATIVE PROMPT)

Bad Artist (THIS GOES INTO YOUR NEGATIVE PROMPT)

Style PaintMagic - Released now! :)

FaeMagic3 - Sorry another embedding of mine that I haven't released, but I will!

Empire Style

WLOP Style LoRA

I believe this is everything, but again very sorry if I missed one!

Where Do I Put Textual Inversions/LORAs/Models/VAE?

Embeddings/Textual Inversions go in Stable Diffusion Folder > Stable-Diffusion-Webui > Embeddings

LORAS go into Stable Diffusion Folder > Stable-Diffusion-Webui>Models>Lora

Models go into Stable Diffusion Folder > Stable-Diffusion-Webui>Models>Stable-diffusion

VAE go into Stable Diffusion Folder > Stable-Diffusion-Webui>Models>VAE (AND THEN YOU TURN VAE ON IN YOUR SETTINGS IN THE A1111 WEBUI)

These instructions are for use of the A1111 WebUI ONLY. I do not use other things and I am not knowledgeable about them, sorry!

I believe this is everything I can think of. Please leave any comments or contact me on discord for anything not here, thank you, and enjoy making beautiful things! :)

items.name: Pixelart Ultramerge
items.description:
Hi,

This is a merge of 30 models in 60 Steps, with the focus on pixel art. No complex prompt engineering necessary, but you can use also complex prompts.

Try different trigger words like: pixelart, sprite, 1-bit till 16-bit,

  • You can play with the weights (range ~ +-2)

  • Not every trigger works for every scenery. While in one just pixelart works great, in the next scene you need to weight the trigger. And in the next one you will need to use it together with negative prompts.

  • Use border, mosaic, voxel as negative (separated or combined). It can help, if it looks some kind of blocky. Then you will need also to raise the positive weights for the trigger words.

  • For some combinations, it doesn't seem really to work. Try to enforce it with the own pixel art Lora (in downloads ~18mb) and (mosaic, voxel:0.0) (and -1 sometimes also gives a good result") negative prompt. The voxel and mosaic style seems hardly to interfere with the pixel art style. If somebody knows how to subtract these values from the model, maybe the quality can be improved(Is it maybe some kind of unet issue?).

  • Try to use luisa_pinguins Pixelart Lora, to improve the output in these hard cases https://civitai.com/models/10706/luisap-pixel-art-lora pixelart in the prompt trigger it.

  • Use luise_pinguins Pixelart Lora to get more/other/fancy results. Range +1.4 ~ -1

  • Anti Burn plugin for Automatic1111 can improve the quality, if you smooth down steps.

The model is not perfect. But there are also nice outcomes through imperfection. Sometimes it mixes pixel art and non pixel art. From time to time, you will have borders around chars or mosaiclike pixel art.

You can try to trigger specific styles:

  • Nvinkpunk;

  • modern disney style

  • classic disney style

  • dreamlike

  • samdoesarts

  • charliebo artstyle

items.name: Hyperpreg - Concept
items.description:
I guess you could also use this for inflation, vore, and stuffing? But it was intended for hyperpreg and will do that best.

Please Read Below for Important Info

To activate this LORA, the tokens "pregnant" and "hyperpreg" should be added to your prompt. Your prompt should ideally be something to the effect of "masterpiece, highest quality, girl, pregnant, hyperpreg, big belly," and then the rest of the details of the image. The big belly token is optional, but I've found it to generate a belly that's actually connected to the character's body more often than without it. I've gotten just big balls of pregnancy on occasion, sometimes it's floating just beside the girl, sometimes she's holding it? So I would definitely recommend the tag. It also adds a noticeable bit of weight to some characters in my experience, but your mileage may vary.

This LORA was trained with NAI as a base and will thus work best with that setup. I've gotten my best results by using a weight of 1, but I also haven't experimented very much with weight values.

Just a fair warning, you're probably not going to get very many interesting poses with this LORA. Hyperpreg is not a genre of fetish well known for a variety of character poses.

modelVersions.name: v2
modelVersions.description:
This version has been trained off of roughly 1000 images, with enough variety of art styles that your generations without any artist LORAs should come out pretty plain looking-- which, if you want a good base to add LORAs to, is a good thing in my opinion.

That being said, considering the quality of hyperpreg images online, your faces might come out a bit more warped than usual on the first go around. Just be prepared to do a bit of inpainting on some artist LORAs.

Source images range in size from octomom to omegapreg, and additionally range in shape from smooth and circular to bumpy and oblong. Also occasionally generates images with stretch marks if you're into that.

The world wildest (and funnist)cat ,Training based on 167 photo samples.

you can also download this model from here:https://tusi.art/u/604280638463365823

The Pallas's cat (Otocolobus manul), also known as the manul, is a small wild cat with long and dense light grey fur, native to mountainous regions across central Asia. Its head-and-body length ranges from 46 to 65 cm (18 to 26 in) with a 21 to 31 cm (8.3 to 12.2 in) long bushy tail. It is well camouflaged and adapted to the cold continental climate in its native range, which receives little rainfall and experiences a wide range of temperatures.

The Pallas's cat was first described in 1776 by Peter Simon Pallas, who observed it in the vicinity of Lake Baikal. To date, it has been recorded across a large areal extent, albeit in widely spaced sites from Caucasus in the west to South Siberian Mountains in the east. It inhabits rocky montane grasslands and shrublands, where the snow cover is below 15–20 cm (6–8 in). It finds shelter in rock crevices and burrows, and preys foremost on lagomorphs and rodents. The female gives birth to between two and six kittens in spring.

Due to its widespread range and assumed large population, the Pallas's cat has been listed as Least Concern on the IUCN Red List since 2020. Some population units are threatened by poaching, prey base decline due to rodent control programs, and habitat fragmentation as a result of mining and infrastructure projects. The Pallas's cat has been kept in zoos since the early 1950s. As of 2018, 60 zoos in Europe, Russia, North America and Japan participate in Pallas's cat captive breeding programs.

modelVersions.name: v2.1
modelVersions.description: Actually, I've been testing the 1500-step version and it seems much improved, so I'm uploading this one too. While testing, I've sometimes found results that make me think the TI's on the verge of being overtrained, so I will stop training this model here.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: I'm uploading an alternate model that feels more accurate, in my opinion. I've altered my working process a little bit in the last few days. First of all, I don't use the "Use PNG alpha channel as loss weight" anymore, as I felt my embeddings were getting overtrained almost from the start. I have a more active approach now too: I begin with a flat learning rate of around 0.004 and patiently wait until I get some decent pic resembling the subject, which usually doesn't take more than 400 steps anyway. Then I interrupt the process, test the result and reduce the learning rate to maybe 0.001. Run the process for a few more hundred steps and usually I already get a decent TI at least. I guess I'll keep improving the process as I run more tests, but for the time being I'm happy with these results. Hope you like it!

items.name: Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)
items.description:
LoRA of Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

BAKUSHIN~ BAKUSHIN~ BAKUSHIN~

Notice : Her floral eyes are dimly(?) visible.

Recommend options

  • LoRA weight 0.7~0.9

  • Trigger words

    • base

      • sakura bakushin o \(umamusume\)

    • Racing competition clothes :

      • epaulettes, sleeveless shirt, pink shirt, sailor collar, capelet, yellow neckerchief, asymmetrical gloves, mismatched gloves, black gloves, white gloves, black shorts, white thighhighs, asymmetrical footwear, mismatched footwear, high heel boots

      • (optional) smile, smiling eyes,

      • If you want to shrink prompts, remove below

        • asymmetrical footwear, high heel boots, asymmetrical gloves, black gloves, white gloves

    • Tracen school uniform :

      • white thighhighs, tracen school uniform, purple shirt, pleated skirt, puffy short sleeves, white skirt, puffy sleeves, summer uniform, frilled skirt, sailor collar, sailor shirt, miniskirt, frills

    • Casual clothes :

      • white shorts, short shorts, open clothes, blue jacket, open jacket, black shirt, long sleeves, shirt tucked in, floral print, casual

Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use highres. fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler : Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss. Thank you a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 116 images of sakura bakushin o

    • 4x low quality 46 images

    • 8x medium quality 31 images

    • 16x high quality 39 images

    • => 1 epoch = 1056 images

  • replaced character feature tags with sakura bakushin o \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, pink eyes, etc.

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • batch size = 4, 7 epochs trained

  • other training settings included in training_data.zip

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

items.name: GV-mix
items.description:
Grilled Vegetable mix

  • GV-mix-O(original, fp32, yes-ema)

  • GV-mix-L(lite, fp16, no-ema)

  • A little different face shape.

  • The thickness of the body is well expressed, creating a good sense of depth.

  • The pupils come out beautifully.

  • Skilled at drawing fingers.(maybe...)

  • Excellent at cooking.

  • not bad backgrounds.

  • I'm sorry. I don't remember which model I used.

Recommended Settings

  • Clip skip : 2

  • SD VAE : kl-f8-anime2

  • P : (best quality, masterpiece:1.4)

  • NP : (low quality, worst quality:1.4), EasyNegative #use EasyNegative Embedding

  • Sampler : DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps : 25

  • CFG : 7~12

  • Hires upscaler : R-ESRGAN 4x+ anime6B

  • upscale : 2~3

  • Denoising strength : 0.4~0.65

items.name: Genshin Impact Cyno Lora
items.description: This Lora was made using 35 picked images from Cyno and used Anything V4.5, it uses common booru tags and can be called with "Cyno". To get more of the details add "animal hat, loincloth, dark skinned male, platinum hair" the best values are between 0.6-0.8.

items.name: Lucario Lora
items.description: This Lora was trained with 52 images from boorus, trying to balance male and female versions. To trigger Lucario, use "lucario, wolf, spikes, blue fur" and for the egyptian set use "egyptian". Works well in Anything V4.5 but should be used in other furry related models.

items.name: Drooling on sleep Lora (Anime)
items.description:
This Lora is mostly a test to do a small Lora model using the recipe made by LuisaP.

This one was trained with 35 images of close up of characters sleeping and drooling saliva, so the results might be more towards close ups than full bodies. Maybe can be acceptable for in-painting.

Check the examples to get an idea what the prompting should work, but normally should work with "drooling, saliva, sleep"
